WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.857 align:middle line:90%


00:00:12.857 --> 00:00:15.550 align:middle line:84%
>> Certain images
can sum up a city--

00:00:15.550 --> 00:00:17.980 align:middle line:84%
the poor river
sides of Calcutta,

00:00:17.980 --> 00:00:23.830 align:middle line:84%
the undernourished children,
and its dilapidated buildings.

00:00:23.830 --> 00:00:27.760 align:middle line:84%
But for the last 20 years,
scenes from Indian cities

00:00:27.760 --> 00:00:31.120 align:middle line:84%
have been shaken by the arrival
of American-style shopping

00:00:31.120 --> 00:00:32.170 align:middle line:90%
centers.

00:00:32.170 --> 00:00:34.585 align:middle line:84%
Like this one, filled
by Western brands.

00:00:34.585 --> 00:00:36.840 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:36.840 --> 00:00:42.840 align:middle line:90%


00:00:42.840 --> 00:00:52.340 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:00:52.340 --> 00:00:55.355 align:middle line:90%
>> Move, make room.

00:00:55.355 --> 00:00:57.880 align:middle line:84%
The city mayor and
a minister have

00:00:57.880 --> 00:01:00.760 align:middle line:84%
come to the opening with one
of the most famous actors

00:01:00.760 --> 00:01:02.603 align:middle line:90%
on the Indian subcontinent.

00:01:02.603 --> 00:01:09.020 align:middle line:90%


00:01:09.020 --> 00:01:11.900 align:middle line:84%
Welcome to the Paradise of
shopping and gastronomy.

00:01:11.900 --> 00:01:18.780 align:middle line:90%


00:01:18.780 --> 00:01:21.800 align:middle line:84%
Upstairs next to
traditional foods,

00:01:21.800 --> 00:01:25.350 align:middle line:84%
three Western fast food
brands are about to open--

00:01:25.350 --> 00:01:31.650 align:middle line:84%
Subway, KFC, and soon, Domino's
Pizza, the brand's 600th point

00:01:31.650 --> 00:01:32.630 align:middle line:90%
of sale in India.

00:01:32.630 --> 00:01:37.920 align:middle line:90%


00:01:37.920 --> 00:01:38.970 align:middle line:90%
How much is it?

00:01:38.970 --> 00:01:40.870 align:middle line:90%
59 rupees, sir.

00:01:40.870 --> 00:01:42.530 align:middle line:90%
59 rupees, OK.

00:01:42.530 --> 00:01:46.110 align:middle line:90%
59 rupees, 80 euro cents.

00:01:46.110 --> 00:01:49.680 align:middle line:84%
It's a Western product at a
very low price, the main sales

00:01:49.680 --> 00:01:51.028 align:middle line:90%
argument of the brand.

00:01:51.028 --> 00:01:52.320 align:middle line:90%
And that are some even cheaper.

00:01:52.320 --> 00:01:55.790 align:middle line:90%


00:01:55.790 --> 00:01:59.480 align:middle line:84%
>> This pizza is a [? steady ?]
[INAUDIBLE] for Domino's.

00:01:59.480 --> 00:02:02.960 align:middle line:84%
And the main thing is,
like, we [INAUDIBLE]

00:02:02.960 --> 00:02:05.185 align:middle line:90%
this pizza is only at 49.

00:02:05.185 --> 00:02:06.560 align:middle line:84%
That is
[? the thing about it. ?]

00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:09.990 align:middle line:84%
So that's why it's
the most popular.

00:02:09.990 --> 00:02:13.180 align:middle line:84%
[INAUDIBLE] 49 is like
dream comes true, I think.

00:02:13.180 --> 00:02:16.840 align:middle line:84%
[INAUDIBLE] and for
the guest, also.

00:02:16.840 --> 00:02:20.170 align:middle line:84%
>> Industrial food is still the
stuff of dreams in developing

00:02:20.170 --> 00:02:22.795 align:middle line:84%
countries and they
are promising markets.

00:02:22.795 --> 00:02:27.030 align:middle line:90%


00:02:27.030 --> 00:02:31.770 align:middle line:84%
In France and Europe, this
fairy tale is less of a success.

00:02:31.770 --> 00:02:34.380 align:middle line:84%
Safety campaigns
against junk food

00:02:34.380 --> 00:02:36.090 align:middle line:90%
have been shown for 15 years.

00:02:36.090 --> 00:02:39.070 align:middle line:90%


00:02:39.070 --> 00:02:42.130 align:middle line:84%
>> By eating less sugar and
fat, you can help to protect

00:02:42.130 --> 00:02:44.260 align:middle line:90%
your health.

00:02:44.260 --> 00:02:48.460 align:middle line:84%
>> In 2004, a law was voted
to limit the effects of food

00:02:48.460 --> 00:02:50.613 align:middle line:90%
marketing.

00:02:50.613 --> 00:02:52.030 align:middle line:84%
And the adverts
for these products

00:02:52.030 --> 00:02:54.760 align:middle line:84%
will have to contain health
warnings by law in an effort

00:02:54.760 --> 00:02:56.650 align:middle line:90%
to combat obesity.

00:02:56.650 --> 00:02:59.930 align:middle line:84%
For good health, avoid
eating too much sugar, fat,

00:02:59.930 --> 00:03:02.470 align:middle line:84%
or salt. Under
pressure, industries

00:03:02.470 --> 00:03:06.190 align:middle line:84%
reduced the quantities of sugar,
salt, and fat in their products

00:03:06.190 --> 00:03:07.600 align:middle line:90%
in France.

00:03:07.600 --> 00:03:10.940 align:middle line:84%
But they still find ways to
get around this obstacle.

00:03:10.940 --> 00:03:13.570 align:middle line:84%
Online, where ads
are less regulated,

00:03:13.570 --> 00:03:16.240 align:middle line:90%
they target new consumers.

00:03:16.240 --> 00:03:19.390 align:middle line:84%
In countries in the South,
brands go even further,

00:03:19.390 --> 00:03:20.500 align:middle line:90%
even going into schools.

00:03:20.500 --> 00:03:23.140 align:middle line:90%


00:03:23.140 --> 00:03:25.750 align:middle line:84%
And load their products
with fat and sugar.

00:03:25.750 --> 00:03:29.750 align:middle line:90%


00:03:29.750 --> 00:03:32.650 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't know whether
this would be [INAUDIBLE]..

00:03:32.650 --> 00:03:36.100 align:middle line:84%
>> Investigation into the new
territories of the fast food

00:03:36.100 --> 00:03:37.510 align:middle line:90%
giants.

00:03:37.510 --> 00:03:40.540 align:middle line:84%
>> In India, they moved
to no food to bad food.

00:03:40.540 --> 00:03:42.680 align:middle line:84%
It is going to be disastrous
for public health.

00:03:42.680 --> 00:04:07.890 align:middle line:90%


00:04:07.890 --> 00:04:10.080 align:middle line:84%
>> When you think
of Rio de Janeiro,

00:04:10.080 --> 00:04:12.220 align:middle line:90%
some images always come to mind.

00:04:12.220 --> 00:04:15.810 align:middle line:90%


00:04:15.810 --> 00:04:19.620 align:middle line:84%
Copacabana Beach, sculpted
bodies, easy living.

00:04:19.620 --> 00:04:23.000 align:middle line:90%


00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:25.100 align:middle line:90%
And a passion for sport.

00:04:25.100 --> 00:04:28.880 align:middle line:84%
These common themes are often
exploited by Western brands,

00:04:28.880 --> 00:04:31.760 align:middle line:90%
especially for fizzy drinks.

00:04:31.760 --> 00:04:34.640 align:middle line:84%
Football, favelas,
and sugary drinks.

00:04:34.640 --> 00:04:41.990 align:middle line:90%


00:04:41.990 --> 00:04:44.440 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:44.440 --> 00:04:49.860 align:middle line:90%


00:04:49.860 --> 00:04:53.240 align:middle line:84%
But the reality in Brazil
is that one in two adults

00:04:53.240 --> 00:04:55.895 align:middle line:84%
are overweight and one
in seven are obese.

00:04:55.895 --> 00:04:58.690 align:middle line:90%


00:04:58.690 --> 00:05:01.430 align:middle line:84%
And according to this
spokesperson for a consumer

00:05:01.430 --> 00:05:05.300 align:middle line:84%
association, fizzy drink brands
cannot consider themselves

00:05:05.300 --> 00:05:06.710 align:middle line:90%
blameless.

00:05:06.710 --> 00:05:09.440 align:middle line:84%
>> Excessive marketing is one
of the main reasons for the rise

00:05:09.440 --> 00:05:10.520 align:middle line:90%
in obesity here.

00:05:10.520 --> 00:05:13.380 align:middle line:84%
Children become addicted
from a very early age.

00:05:13.380 --> 00:05:15.560 align:middle line:84%
And then it's much harder
to wean them off it.

00:05:15.560 --> 00:05:18.740 align:middle line:84%
They drink a lot of fizzy
drinks before the age of two,

00:05:18.740 --> 00:05:20.600 align:middle line:90%
even from their baby bottle.

00:05:20.600 --> 00:05:23.210 align:middle line:84%
Parents give this type of
product to their children

00:05:23.210 --> 00:05:26.270 align:middle line:84%
because they believe that if
adverts and businesses promote

00:05:26.270 --> 00:05:28.550 align:middle line:84%
them so much, it
can't be harmful.

00:05:28.550 --> 00:05:30.590 align:middle line:84%
Brazil is the third
biggest market

00:05:30.590 --> 00:05:32.090 align:middle line:90%
in the world for Coca-Cola.

00:05:32.090 --> 00:05:36.560 align:middle line:90%


00:05:36.560 --> 00:05:38.690 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:05:38.690 --> 00:05:43.170 align:middle line:90%


00:05:43.170 --> 00:05:46.680 align:middle line:84%
>> The truth is that
I love fizzy drink.

00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:48.280 align:middle line:90%
I'm addicted.

00:05:48.280 --> 00:05:52.320 align:middle line:84%
We drink it nearly every day
at home and also when I go out.

00:05:52.320 --> 00:05:55.600 align:middle line:90%


00:05:55.600 --> 00:05:57.600 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:05:57.600 --> 00:06:00.120 align:middle line:84%
>> It's my grandson
who likes them a lot.

00:06:00.120 --> 00:06:02.910 align:middle line:84%
The big bottles are for me
and the little ones for him.

00:06:02.910 --> 00:06:04.740 align:middle line:84%
He takes them straight
out of the fridge

00:06:04.740 --> 00:06:07.110 align:middle line:84%
and it's exactly the
size of his little hand.

00:06:07.110 --> 00:06:12.120 align:middle line:90%


00:06:12.120 --> 00:06:14.016 align:middle line:90%
>> Crisps.

00:06:14.016 --> 00:06:15.750 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:15.750 --> 00:06:19.320 align:middle line:84%
In Brazil, there is no
law around food marketing

00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:22.260 align:middle line:84%
so brands don't hesitate to
[INAUDIBLE] [? for clients ?]

00:06:22.260 --> 00:06:23.580 align:middle line:90%
from school age.

00:06:23.580 --> 00:06:26.930 align:middle line:84%
Belo Horizonte, the sixth
biggest city in the country.

00:06:26.930 --> 00:06:34.730 align:middle line:90%


00:06:34.730 --> 00:06:37.840 align:middle line:84%
These neighborhoods in the
hills and this public college

